    Use LaTeX for all mathematical documentation in docstrings.

    Viscosity Model: Carreau-Yasuda: Œº(Œ≥Àô‚Äã)=Œº‚àû‚Äã+(Œº0‚Äã‚àíŒº‚àû‚Äã)[1+(ŒªŒ≥Àô‚Äã)a]an‚àí1‚Äã.

    Loss Function: Ltotal‚Äã=ŒªD‚ÄãLData‚Äã+ŒªNS‚ÄãLNS‚Äã+ŒªBrink‚ÄãLBrinkman‚Äã+ŒªRheo‚ÄãLRheo‚Äã.

Coding Standards

    Mesh Agnosticism: Always assume unstructured graphs G=(V,E). Do not hardcode grid dimensions.

    Dimensionality: Default to 2D (u,v,p,œï,Œº) unless 3D is explicitly requested.

    Variable Naming: Use u for velocity, p for pressure, phi for thrombus phase-field, and gamma_dot for shear rate.

    DEQ Solvers: Prefer Anderson Acceleration or Broyden's method for fixed-point iterations.

    Soft-Logic: Use Sigmoidal Gates for biochemical triggers to ensure ‚àá stability.

Specialized Instructions

    When writing loss functions, always include the residual of the Navier-Stokes equations as a penalty.

    Ensure all LoRA layers are applied only to the GNN/GINO weights, leaving the physics-informed kernels frozen during Tier 3.

Testing & Validation (Mandatory)

    Verified Additions: Every new function, layer, or loss term must be accompanied by a pytest unit test before being considered "done."

    Mesh-Agnostic Validation: Tests must pass on graphs with varying node/edge counts to ensure no hardcoded dimensions exist.

    Physical Sanity Checks: - Verify Carreau-Yasuda outputs against Œº0‚Äã and Œº‚àû‚Äã limits.

        Validate Navier-Stokes residuals against a simple analytical case (e.g., Poiseuille flow) to ensure the implementation of the differential operators is correct.

    Convergence Guard: For DEQ updates, include a test to verify that the fixed-point solver converges within 10‚àí5 tolerance on a standard forward pass.

    Gradient Integrity: Use torch.autograd.gradcheck or similar assertions to ensure that custom loss terms do not produce vanishing or exploding gradients.